[
  {
    "id": "lux-inhername",
    "title": "LUX: #InHerName",
    "brand": "LUX",
    "agency": "VML",
    "tags": [
      "Integrated Campaign",
      "Social"
    ],
    "award": "Cannes Shortlist",
    "awardType": "shortlist",
    "featured": true,
    "hero": {
      "type": "vimeo",
      "vimeoId": "76979871",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504711434969-e33886168f5c?w=1200&q=80"
    },
    "intro": {
      "headline": "Reclaiming a name that was never hers to lose.",
      "year": "2024",
      "role": "Senior Copywriter",
      "body": [
        "In many parts of Asia, a woman's name disappears the moment she marries. She becomes \"Wife of\", \"Mother of\", \"Daughter-in-law of\" — her own identity quietly erased by tradition.",
        "For International Women's Day 2024, LUX asked a simple but radical question: what if we gave those names back?",
        "#InHerName was an integrated campaign that invited women across the region to reclaim their names publicly — through social, film, and community activations that sparked a genuine cultural conversation."
      ]
    },
    "assetsLayout": "right-column",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "The Insight",
        "body": "Across Southeast Asia, millions of women stop being called by their given names after marriage. It's social erosion — slow, unremarkable, almost universally accepted. That invisibility became our brief."
      },
      {
        "heading": "The Idea",
        "body": "Rather than tell women their names matter, we created a platform for them to prove it. #InHerName invited real women to share the stories behind their names — and challenged their communities to use them, out loud and in full."
      },
      {
        "heading": "The Work",
        "body": "A hero film anchored the campaign, following three women across three countries. Social content, influencer partnerships, and in-market activations extended the conversation across the region."
      }
    ],
    "assets": [
      {
        "type": "image",
        "url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1611162616305-c69b3fa7fbe0?w=1200&q=80",
        "caption": "Campaign key visual"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1478720568477-152d9b164e26?w=1200&q=80",
        "caption": "Hero film still"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504711434969-e33886168f5c?w=1200&q=80",
        "caption": "Social executions"
      }
    ],
    "awards": [
      "Cannes Lions Shortlist 2024 — Social & Influencer",
      "Cannes Lions Shortlist 2024 — Culture & Context",
      "Gold — Epica Awards 2024",
      "Bronze — London International Awards 2024",
      "Merit — The One Show 2025",
      "Bronze — Spikes Asia 2025"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "hsbc-mind-athletes",
    "title": "HSBC Mind Athletes",
    "brand": "HSBC",
    "agency": "VML",
    "tags": [
      "Experiential",
      "Event",
      "Gaming"
    ],
    "award": "Gold ×5 MEA 2025",
    "awardType": "gold",
    "featured": true,
    "hero": {
      "type": "vimeo",
      "vimeoId": "148751763",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1529699211952-734e80c4d42b?w=1200&q=80"
    },
    "intro": {
      "headline": "What if your finances were something you trained for?",
      "year": "2024",
      "role": "Senior Copywriter",
      "body": [
        "Most financial campaigns talk at people. HSBC wanted to talk with them — and specifically with Singapore's most analytically gifted minds.",
        "Mind Athletes was an experiential campaign built around competitive chess, positioning HSBC Premier as a partner for people who think several moves ahead."
      ]
    },
    "assetsLayout": "below",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "The Challenge",
        "body": "HSBC Premier needed to resonate with high-net-worth individuals immune to generic financial messaging. We needed a platform that felt earned, not advertised."
      },
      {
        "heading": "The Idea",
        "body": "Chess players are elite strategists — deeply underserved by brands. We partnered with Singapore's chess community to create Mind Athletes: events, content, and conversations that put strategy at the centre of financial thinking."
      }
    ],
    "assets": [
      {
        "type": "image",
        "url": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1529699211952-734e80c4d42b?w=1200&q=80",
